Sentencas: The calcium cobaltite Ca(3-x)La(x)Co(4-y)CuyO(9+delta) with x and y = 0 and 0.1 were synthesized and the electrical, thermal, and catalytic behaviors for the oxygen reduction reaction (ORR) for use as air electrodes in intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs) were evaluated.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of Ca3-xLaxCo4-yCuyO9+δ cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: X-ray diffraction confirms the Ca(3-x)La(x)Co(4-y)CuyO(9+delta) samples were crystallized in a monoclinic structure and scanning electron microscopic image shows lamella-like grain formation.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of Ca3-xLaxCo4-yCuyO9+δ cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Introduction of dopants decreases slightly the loss of lattice oxygen and thermal expansion co-efficient.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of Ca3-xLaxCo4-yCuyO9+δ cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The Ca(3-x)La(x)Co(4-y)CuyO(9+delta) samples exhibit good phase stability for long-term operation, thermal expansion, and chemical compatibility with the Ce0.8Gd0.2O2-delta electrolyte.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of Ca3-xLaxCo4-yCuyO9+δ cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Among the studied samples, Ca2.9La0.1Co4O9+delta shows a maximum conductivity of 176 Scm(-1) at 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of Ca3-xLaxCo4-yCuyO9+δ cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Although the doped samples exhibit a higher total electrical conductivity, an improved symmetrical cell performance is displayed by the undoped sample.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of Ca3-xLaxCo4-yCuyO9+δ cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Comparing the sintering temperatures, the composite cathode Ca3Co4O9+delta + Ce0.8Gd0.2O2-delta sintered at 800 degrees C exhibit the lowest area specific resistance of 0.154 Omega cm(2) at 800 degrees C in air.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of Ca3-xLaxCo4-yCuyO9+δ cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In the Ca(3-x)La(x)Co4-yCuyO(9+delta) + GDC composite cathodes, the charge-transfer process at high frequencies presents a major rate limiting step for the oxygen reduction reaction.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of Ca3-xLaxCo4-yCuyO9+δ cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
